   VERSION=( 1.5 1.4.2 )
    IGNORE='shishi'
  CATEGORY='network/chat network/ftp'
 ATTRIBUTE='client console server'
    SOURCE="inetutils/inetutils-$VERSION.tar.gz"
       URL="$GNU_URL"
  HOMEPAGE='http://www.gnu.org/software/inetutils/inetutils.html'
       REQ=( 'db e2fsprogs ncurses readline zlib'
             'Linux-PAM:--with-pam:--without-pam:for pluggable authentication'
             'heimdal:--with-krb5:--without-krb5:for heimdal kerberos 5 support'
             'openssl:::for secure socket connect support'
             'shishi:--with-shishi:--without-shishi:for shishi kerberos 5 support'
             'tcp_wrappers:--with-wrap:--without-wrap:for tcp wrapper support'
             'xinetd:::for launching servers upon demand'
             '::--disable-ftp:Compile and install ftp'
             '::--disable-ping:Compile and install ping'
             '::--disable-ping6:Compile and install ping6'
             '::--disable-rcp:Compile and install rcp'
             '::--disable-rlogin:Compile and install rlogin'
             '::--disable-rsh:Compile and install rsh'
             '::--disable-talk:Compile and install talk'
             '::--disable-telnet:Compile and install telnet'
             '::--disable-tftp:Compile and install tftp'
             '::--disable-ftpd:Compile and install ftpd'
             '::--disable-inetd:Compile and install inetd'
             '::--disable-rexecd:Compile and install rexecd'
             '::--disable-rlogind:Compile and install rlogind'
             '::--disable-rshd:Compile and install rshd'
             '::--disable-talkd:Compile and install talkd'
             '::--disable-telnetd:Compile and install telnetd'
             '::--disable-tftpd:Compile and install tftpd'
             '::--disable-uucpd:Compile and install uucpd' )
      OPTS='--disable-syslogd --disable-ifconfig --disable-whois --disable-logger'
# should ifconfig whois and/or syslogd from inetutils be supported?
  ESTIMATE='1200'
      DESC='inetutils contains the netkit networking tools.
Clients: ftp ping rpc rlogin rsh talk telnet tftp
Servers: ftpd inetd rexecd rlogind rshd talkd telnetd tftpd uucpd

The ftp, ping, telent, and tftp clients may be useful occasionally.
The servers are definitely not worth using unless you live in a
country that prevents use of ssh/sshd strong encryption methods
for secure logins.

Unlike netkit-combo this spell does not invoke
any of the servers automatically from xinetd.
SA would likely run any of these servers
within a chrooted or caged file system
rather than allowing full access to the box.'
